Day 5: Conditional Rendering

Conditional Rendering means displaying different UI based on a condition.

Example:

User logged in → Show Welcome message.
User not logged in → Show Login button.
1. Using if-else
function Login() {

    const isLoggedIn = true;

    if (isLoggedIn) {
        return <h2>Welcome Priyadharshini</h2>;
    }

    return <h2>Please Login</h2>;
}

export default Login;
Output
Welcome Priyadharshini
2. Using Ternary Operator

Syntax:

condition ? trueValue : falseValue

Example:

function Login() {

    const isLoggedIn = false;

    return (
        <div>
            {
                isLoggedIn
                    ? <h2>Welcome User</h2>
                    : <h2>Please Login</h2>
            }
        </div>
    );
}

export default Login;

Output:

Please Login
3. Using && Operator

Show something only when condition is true.

function App() {

    const isAdmin = true;

    return (
        <div>
            <h2>Dashboard</h2>

            {isAdmin && <button>Delete User</button>}
        </div>
    );
}

Output:

Dashboard
Delete User

If:

const isAdmin = false;

Output:

Dashboard

Button won't appear.

4. Conditional Rendering with useState
import { useState } from "react";

function LoginStatus() {

    const [isLoggedIn, setIsLoggedIn] = useState(false);

    return (
        <div>

            <h2>
                {
                    isLoggedIn
                        ? "Welcome Priyadharshini"
                        : "Please Login"
                }
            </h2>

            <button
                onClick={() => setIsLoggedIn(!isLoggedIn)}
            >
                Toggle Login
            </button>

        </div>
    );
}

export default LoginStatus;
Real-world Example
Show/Hide Password
import { useState } from "react";

function Password() {

    const [showPassword, setShowPassword] =
        useState(false);

    return (
        <div>

            <input
                type={
                    showPassword
                        ? "text"
                        : "password"
                }
            />

            <button
                onClick={() =>
                    setShowPassword(!showPassword)
                }
            >
                {
                    showPassword
                        ? "Hide"
                        : "Show"
                }
            </button>

        </div>
    );
}

export default Password;
